node.title: Senate committee debates Jackson's Supreme Court nomination
node.description: The committee is expected to deadlock on Jackson's nomination, forcing an additional procedural vote to advance it to the full Senate.

node.title: Olivia Rodrigo has ASL interpreter on Grammys red carpet
node.description: Several other attendees were seen with ASL interpreters too, including country star Mickey Guyton and singer-songwriter Elle King.

node.title: Russian troops tortured, killed mayor and her family, Ukraine says
node.description: Deputy prime minister says the mayor of a village near Kyiv was "killed in captivity" along with her husband and her son by occupying Russian forces.

node.title: Starbucks suspends stock buyback program, interim CEO says
node.description: Interim CEO Howard Schultz said it's time to redirect funds to "invest more profit into our people and our stores."

node.title: Biden calls for stricter gun laws after Sacramento mass shooting
node.description: Six people were killed and 12 others were injured when police say at least two people opened fire outside crowded bars in the downtown district.

node.title: JPMorgan's Jamie Dimon says economy faces "unprecedented" risks
node.description: High inflation and Russia's Ukraine war may "dramatically increase the risks ahead," Dimon wrote in his annual shareholder letter.

node.title: Man confronts anxiety disorder that restricted his life to one mile from home
node.description: Cecil Jackson said the best way to describe agorophobia is feeling like he's living in a glass box — "like there are walls and boundaries that I cannot get past."

node.title: Trump endorses Sarah Palin in run for Alaska's congressional seat
node.description: "Sarah has been a champion for Alaska values, Alaska energy, Alaska jobs, and the great people of Alaska," Trump said.

node.title: Obama to join Biden at first White House event since leaving office
node.description: The former president will appear at an event celebrating the Affordable Care Act, his signature law that passed 12 years ago

node.title: Ukrainian refugees at U.S. border in Mexico: "Just hope... and pray"
node.description: The refugee crisis created by Russia's invasion of Ukraine has come to America's doorstep, with hundreds of refugees arriving in Tijuana to make their way to the San Ysidro port of entry.

node.title: U.S. said to seize mega yacht owned by oligarch who's close to Putin
node.description: It would be the first such seizure by U.S. authorities since Ukraine war-linked sanctions were imposed on the Kremlin.

node.title: Elon Musk buys nearly $3 billion stake in Twitter
node.description: Tesla CEO, who has raised questions about the social media platform's policies, is purchasing 9.2% of Twitter's shares.

node.title: China defends policy of separating COVID-positive kids from parents
node.description: Officials in China's biggest city of Shanghai have refused to budge from the draconian "zero-COVID" policies despite mounting anger.

node.title: Man linked to 1980s rapes by DNA on bill gets 650 years in prison
node.description: Steven Ray Hessler "derived great pleasure from his unnecessarily brutal methods of terrorizing and sexually torturing his victims," prosecutors said.

node.title: Russia denies massacring civilians in town near Ukraine's capital
node.description: Moscow dismisses the latest reported atrocities as a faked "provocation," as the U.S. says it's helping gather evidence of war crimes committed by Putin's troops.

node.title: Mystery surrounds dozens of unmarked graves at former plantation
node.description: In an effort to figure out who is buried in the graves, archaeologists and park staff are reaching out to the public for help.

node.title: 3 dead after shooting, dramatic police chase on beach in Mexico
node.description: Video posted on social media showed people running down the beach as gunshots rang out as others took cover behind tables or chairs.

node.title: Sri Lanka's cabinet ministers resign
node.description: Sri Lanka's cabinet ministers have resigned en masse after protests over the government's handling of the worst economic crisis in decades.

node.title: Paul Coll retains his British Open title
node.description: New Zealand's Paul Coll has defended his British Open squash title with a comprehensive straight game win over Egyptian Ali Farag.

node.title: Man allegedly got up to 90 COVID vaccine shots to sell the cards
node.description: The man in the eastern German city of Magdeburg is accused of getting the injections so he could sell the vaccine cards that went with them. No word on impact on his health.

node.title: Thousands of weekend U.S. flight cancelations carry into workweek
node.description: Airlines were blaming bad Florida weather during spring break for many of their problems.

node.title: Royal NZ Ballet cancels Swan Lake national tour
node.description: The company says the tour would not be viable under the ongoing red traffic light settings, even with indoor gatherings increased to 200 people.

node.title: Some Auckland businesses happy to ditch vaccine passes
node.description: Businesses bidding ka kite to mandatory vaccine pass checks say they are "overjoyed" with the possibility of fewer cancellations, and less work for staff. Audio

node.title: Hungary's nationalist, pro-Putin PM Orban wins 4th term
node.description: The margin of victory was unexpectedly large. The campaign was under a cloud from the Ukraine war, with Orban allowing many Ukrainian refugees into Hungary but striking a neutral and even anti-Ukrainian tone at times.

node.title: Covid-19 update: Nine further deaths and 10,205 new community cases
node.description: There are 10,205 new community cases of Covid-19 and nine further deaths to report today.

node.title: New Zealand will release more oil to contribute to global stock
node.description: New Zealand will release more oil from its emergency stock to offset the global impact of Russia's invasion of Ukraine.

node.title: Marae housing development 'not just about building bricks and mortar'
node.description: A dawn blessing was held today to mark the start of a government-supported development of 20 papakāinga housing units at the Te Āwhina Marae in Motueka.

node.title: On the Farm - a wrap of farming conditions around NZ

node.title: New Zealand couple found dead in Vava'u, Tonga, police say
node.description: Tonga police are reportedly investigating the death of a New Zealand couple in Vava'u.

node.title: South Carolina tops UConn to win women's college basketball title
node.description: The Gamecocks ended the Huskies' undefeated streak in championship games with their 64-49 victory and capped a wire-to-wire run as the No. 1 team in the country in The Associated Press poll.
